content:
Activate, Configure, and Publish FlexCards

After creating a FlexCard, activate it to generate a custom-generated LWC, which you can then add to a Lightning or Experience page.

To activate a FlexCard, see Activate a FlexCard.
To define metadata values, such as where your FlexCard is visible, and to update the component SVG icon for your FlexCard, see Configure Publish Options on a FlexCard.
To add a FlexCard to a Lightning or Experience page, see below:

Lightning page
Add a FlexCard to a Lightning Page

Experience page
Add a FlexCard to an Experience Page

Off-platform (outside of Salesforce)
Beginning in Summer ’21, see OmniOut.

Activate a FlexCard
Activate a FlexCard to generate an LWC and publish it to a Lightning page or Experience Builder site. After you activate a FlexCard, you can’t edit it or add elements to it.

Configure Publish Options on a FlexCard
Define metadata values, such as where your FlexCard is visible, and update the component SVG icon for your FlexCard before publishing your component to a Lighting or Experience page.

Add a FlexCard to a Lightning Page
After creating and activating your FlexCard, publish the generated component to a Lightning page from the Lightning App Builder.

Add a FlexCard to an Experience Page
After creating and activating your FlexCard, publish the generated component to an Experience page from the Experience Builder.
title: Activating and Publishing FlexCards in Salesforce
